ible equivalent error sets. By\ncombining this error set selection with the genetic algorithm approach, we have\nfound $((11,68))$ and $((11,80))$ codes capable of correcting a single\namplitude damping error and $((11,4))$, $((12,4))$, $((13,8))$, and $((14,16))$\ncodes capable of correcting two amplitude damping\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Jul 2019 07:01:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 5 Oct 2019 15:04:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-11"}
