, while\nthe collision risk of crested ibises could be low, barrier-like structures,\nsuch as fences, should still be considered to promote the conservation of\nmultiple bird species in the area. This paper provides a practical case for\nrailway ecology studies in China. To our best knowledge, this is the first\nhigh-speed railway project that takes protecting crested ibises as one of the\ntop priorities, and exemplifies the recent nationwide initiative towards the\nconstruction of \"eco-civilization\" in the country.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Jul 2019 14:52:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-11"}
